    public abstract class AtomicHIOAwithDE
extends AtomicHIOA
    The class AtomicHIOAwithDE implements hybrid input/output automata where the trajectories of continuous variables are defined by differential equations.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant              true

      • AtomicHIOAwithDE

        public AtomicHIOAwithDE(java.lang.String uri,
                        java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit simulatedTimeUnit,
                        SimulatorI simulationEngine)
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        create an atomic hybrid input/output model based on a differential equations solver with the given URI (if null, one will be generated) and to be run by the given simulator (or by the one of an ancestor coupled model if null) using the given time unit for its clock.

        Contract

         pre     simulatedTimeUnit != null
 pre     simulationEngine == null || simulationEngine instanceof HIOA_AtomicEngine
 post    getURI() != null
 post    uri != null implies this.getURI().equals(uri)
 post    getSimulatedTimeUnit().equals(simulatedTimeUnit)
 post    simulationEngine != null implies getSimulationEngine().equals(simulationEngine)
 post    !isDebugModeOn()
        Parameters:
        uri - unique identifier of the model.
        simulatedTimeUnit - time unit used for the simulation clock.
        simulationEngine - simulation engine enacting the model.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - TODO.

      • produceOutput

        public void produceOutput(Time current)
        Description copied from interface: ModelI
        force the model to forward externals event generated before their next internal transition step.

        Description

        The implementation follows the principle of the "peer message exchanging implementation" i.e., the simulators exchanges directly with each others the exported and imported events without passing by their parent (and ancestors).

        Contract

         pre     current != null
 post   true            // no postcondition.
        Specified by:
        produceOutput in interface ModelI
        Overrides:
        produceOutput in class AtomicModel
        Parameters:
        current - current simulation time at which external events may be output.
